Subject: Resignation – Last Working Day on 31st December

Dear Sir/Madam,

I hope you are doing well.
Please consider this email as my formal resignation from my position at Easy Comm Innovations.

I am grateful for the opportunities, learning, and support I have received during my time here. Working under the guidance of Founder Yogesh Dubey Sir, along with the support of HR Nitika Sadele, Manager Nikke Chhatani, and the entire team has been truly valuable for my professional growth.

As per the notice period, I would like my last working day to be 31st December.
I will ensure a smooth handover of all my responsibilities and tasks before my exit.

Thank you once again for the trust and opportunities.
Wishing the company continued growth and success in the future.

Warm regards,
Hariom Vishwakarma




Resignation Letter

Subject: Resignation Letter

Dear Sir/Mam
I hope you are doing well.
Through this mail, I would like to formally resign from my position at Easy Comm Innovations.

I am thankful for the opportunities, support, guidance, and learning that I received throughout my journey here. Working with Yogesh Dubey sir, HR Nitika ma’am, Nikke sir, and the entire team has been a valuable experience for me.

As per the policy, I understand that the standard notice period is 60 days.
However, I kindly request you to consider making my last working day as 31st December, as it will help me manage my commitments smoothly.

I assure you that I will complete all my pending tasks, documentation, and handover responsibilities properly during the notice period. I am fully committed to ensuring a smooth transition.

Thank you once again for your support and understanding.
I hope my request for an early last working date will be considered.

Warm regards,
Hariom Vishwakarma
Shopify Developer
Easy Comm Innovations